{"id":12309,"date":"2022-07-20T23:51:00","date_gmt":"2022-07-20T23:51:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/?p=12309"},"modified":"2022-07-20T23:51:02","modified_gmt":"2022-07-20T23:51:02","slug":"a-protest-to-end-shared-access-a-ride-trips-and-resume-solo-rides","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/a-protest-to-end-shared-access-a-ride-trips-and-resume-solo-rides\/","title":{"rendered":"A Protest to End Shared Access-a-Ride Trips and Resume Solo Rides"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-container-3 wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-container-1 wp-block-column\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">We\u2019re live with \u2066<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/AARReformGroup?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@AARReformGroup<\/a>\u2069 at \u2066<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/MTA?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@MTA<\/a>\u2069 headquarters demanding an end to dangerous shared paratransit rides! <a href=\"https:\/\/t.co\/tsy0pu8HlB\">pic.twitter.com\/tsy0pu8HlB<\/a><\/p>&mdash; NYLPI (@NYLPI) <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/NYLPI\/status\/1430182183138963468?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">August 24, 2021<\/a><\/blockquote><script async src=\"https:\/\/platform.twitter.com\/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"><\/script>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-2 wp-block-column\">\n<p>A tweet published on August 24th of 2021 shows New York Lawyers for the Public interest and AAARRG! (Access-A-Ride Reform Group) protesting in front of the Metropolitain Transportation Authority (MTA) offices asking to end the shared paratransit rides, in the midst of the Delta wave.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For the 16 months since the beginning of the pandemic, the paratransit rides were offered on a solo basis but now, the MTA claims a driver shortage makes that impossible and seeks to resume \u201cshared rides\u201d. Activists claim that solos rides were safer for riders, but they also made for shorter, easier, and more direct trips than what the paratransit riders call the \u201cfive-borough tours\u201d which lengthened the trips of shared rides.  \u2014Yan Grenier<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>A tweet published on August 24th of 2021 shows New York Lawyers for the Public interest and AAARRG! (Access-A-Ride Reform Group) protesting in front of the Metropolitain Transportation Authority (MTA) offices asking to end the shared paratransit rides, in the midst of the Delta wave. For the 16 months since&hellip; <a class=\"continue\" href=\"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/a-protest-to-end-shared-access-a-ride-trips-and-resume-solo-rides\/\">Continue Reading<span> A Protest to End Shared Access-a-Ride Trips and Resume Solo Rides<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":12310,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"advanced_seo_description":"","jetpack_seo_html_title":"","jetpack_seo_noindex":false,"_FSMCFIC_featured_image_caption":"","_FSMCFIC_featured_image_nocaption":"","_FSMCFIC_featured_image_hide":""},"categories":[44],"tags":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/07\/protest-shared-rides.jpg?fit=2048%2C1536&ssl=1","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/12309"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"hre